<hl>
<seg id=1> Fei Xiaotong Was Awarded Magsaysay Prize </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Manila, August 31 (by Journalist Xiong Changyi) - Doctor Fei Xiaotong, famous Chinese sociologist and Vice Chairman of Standing Committee of National People's Congress, was awarded here this afternoon of Magsaysay "Community Leader" Prize of 1994. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The awarding ceremony was performed solemnly in Philippine Cultural Center. </seg>
<seg id=4> Philippine President Ramos participated the ceremony and awarded medals, bonus, and certificate of merit to six eminent personages who gloriously won the Magsaysay Prize this year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> Fei Xiaotong made a speech of expressing his thanks: "I will never disappoint the encouragement from our friend neighboring country. Whenever how long I can live, I must take full advantage of every minute to do something cautiously and conscientiously to benefit Asian people and even world people, to bring the accumulated knowledge of human being into play of pushing the social developing towards a more beautiful tomorrow." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The Ramon Magsaysay Prize named after former Philippine President was known as the Nobel Prize in Asia. </seg>
<seg id=7> This Prize consists of five items, one time each in a year, to be awarded respectively to individuals and organizations who has made outstanding contributions in the fields of government service, public service, community leader, news, culture and creative communication art and international understanding etc. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Since its start in 1958, totally 172 individuals and 14 organizations have been awarded of this prize. </seg>
</p>
